      "solution": "main :: IO ()\nmain = do\n    s     <- getLine \n    _     <- getLine -- throw line 2 out because we dont need it in haskell \n    perms <- map (map read) . map words . lines <$> getContents :: IO [[Int]]\n    -- perms is reversed in the following because foldr works from right to left \n    -- but the perms were parsed left to right\n    putStrLn $ foldr (\\a b -> map (b!!) a) s (reverse perms)\n\n-- this basically does  \n-- for p in perms:\n--      s' = new char[n]\n--      for i in [0..n-1]: \n--          s'[i] = s[p[i]]\n--      s = s'",
